tip.text: Great lunch place and the staff here are super friendly. The ingredients are fresh and they're all delicious and healthy. I love the beetroot risotto and also the soups and salads here.
Cool furniture store with pieces made from salvaged timber. Minimalistic design and really nice showroom!
Authentic Malaysian dishes. Definitely try the laksa and also the kaya toast!
I've visited a lot of medical museums and this one is just plain creepy. Should be renamed to Museum of Horrible Deaths. Not very educational and some of the exhibits look unkept, eg leaking jars.

formattedAddress: บางกอกน้อย
กรุงเทพมหานคร 10700
location.city: บางกอกน้อย
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

venue.name: Siriraj Medical Museum (พิพิธภัณฑ์การแพทย์ศิริราช)

tip.text: On the weekends, come early to avoid the queue. A good no-fuss dim spot. English menu and pictures provided upon request.

venue.name: DimDimSum Dim Sum Specialty Store (點點心點心專門店)

tip.text: Japanese whiskeys, sakes and fantastic food. Everything on the menu is carefully prepared using fresh ingredients and the service is great! I'm yet to find a dish I don't like. Highly recommended!
Pistachio and earl grey was good, but definitely over-priced.
Large portions and good service.
A magazine library where you can pay per visit or sign up for an annual membership. Nice setting and fantastic selection of magazines from around the world. Friendly & knowledgeable owner.
A haven for jerky-fans. You can find some exotic flavours such as kangaroo, buffalo and crocodile. Do try the pineapple jerky too.
Super casual setting but you'd come here for the food and not the atmosphere. Very fresh seafood and make sure to order the three dots crab.
A modern take to traditional Taiwanese breakfast in a casual, trendy setting. Very good food and must-try is the breakfast egg roll. Crispy and delicious!
Cozy cafe with outdoor seating. Ambient music and quiet enough to chat and read. Also laptop-friendly and great place to get some work done.

formattedAddress: 信義路二段198巷38號 (金華街)

tip.text: A good selection of Taiwanese food but quite pricey. Perfect place to take visitors who might be reluctant to try "re chao" or street food.

venue.name: 欣葉 Shin Yeh Taiwanese Cuisine

tip.text: The scones here are pretty good and are worth the price. I like how they bring out 100 tea samples out just so you can see and smell them all before picking out something.

venue.name: smtih & hsu 現代茶館（天母店）

tip.text: The tsukemen ramen (dipping ramen) is pretty good and do also try the desserts. The layout of the place makes it difficult for larger groups as it's essentially just a bar table.
Vibrant atmosphere and great to sit here on a sunny day to just people watch. I had the vegetarian set lunch from the Hawaiian food truck and it was surprisingly tasty!
Good selection of pasta and starters. Really enjoyed the squid ink pasta and also the roasted vegetables. Great service and cosy atmosphere.
It's really beautiful here and great place for photos during cherry blossom season. Pack a picnic and enjoy the peaceful surrounding.
An open cafe with floor-to-ceiling windows in a nice garden setting at the back of Nezu Museum. Perfect place to get away from the concrete city. The food is delicious too! Do try the desserts.
The chirashi is pretty good and the miso soup is fantastic. Came here during lunch and there was a long line so expect to wait 15mins for a group table.

Fantastic open space that's great for working. Each table is equipped with power outlets and reading lamps. Free wifi and the food is pretty good too. You can also make your own pizza, panini & juice.
Excellent service and friendly staff. The rooms are quite spacious and the small touches add a hint of fun. Great for staycations too as the hotel has everything: spa, pool and restaurant.

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10500
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

tip.text: I can't help but feel this is a tourist trap for middle-aged Westerners. It was nice to take a peek into his home, but would have rather learned more about silk.

formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330
location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

venue.name: The Jim Thompson House (พิพิธภัณฑ์บ้านไทย จิม ทอมป์สัน)

tip.text: Came here for a conference and it felt like one of the saddest places in Taiwan. The rooms are outdated and the hotel restaurant serves mediocre food. The view of the ocean was the only good thing.

venue.name: Howard Beach Resort Green Bay (翡翠灣福華渡假酒店)

tip.text: One of my favorite spots for sashimi bowls. Fresh cuts of fish on a bed of perfectly cooked and seasoned sushi rice. Friendly staff and cosy atmosphere. Get here early for dinner to avoid the queues
Fantastic furniture pieces from Denmark. Can spend hours browsing here. Friendly store owners too!
Unique flavours that are experimental but not too over the top. The meat cuts are cooked to perfection and just melt in your mouth. Book ahead if you want to sit inside.
The mixologists here know how to pour the perfect cocktail. I'm impressed by their gin collection - try Monkey 47. Cosy atmosphere and recommended to sit at the bar if you're not in a group.
Long queues but fast-moving. The chicken rice is good, but nothing exceptional.

formattedAddress: Stall 10, Maxwell Food Centre (1 Kadayanallur St.)

venue.name: Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice 天天海南鸡饭

tip.text: Cute bakery with delicious cakes and cupcakes. They also sell bakeware and books so you can pick up a gift for that sweet tooth friend of yours.
Delicious fresh seafood and a nice view overlooking the ocean. Not very expensive and not too touristy either. Grab a cab from the city -- would be around 20 SGD give or take.

formattedAddress: 1220 East Coast Parkway (Next to Carpark E2)

tip.text: A nice view of the bay upstairs, but it can be a bit loud with Top 40 pop music. Advised not to go when it's raining as the undercover is not quite sheltered from the rain. Service is friendly.
Open-kitchen and everything is freshly prepared on the day. Friendly staff and relaxed atmosphere. Highly recommended for weekend brunch but do book ahead.
Salads are in giant proportions and I can never finish them on my own. Nice atmosphere and friendly staff. Yet to try the brunch here.
The tasting menu is wonderfully delicious. A little bit on the pricey side but worth the treat. This has to be my favourite dessert spot in Taipei. They also serve savoury dishes.

venue.name: 黃檸檬甜點吧 Yellow Lemon

tip.text: A great brunch place. Service can be a bit slow on a busy weekend -- expect meals to come out at different times when you're in a group.
This place only takes reservations Mon-Fri. On the weekends, come early to avoid the lines. They also serve smaller portions of dumplings so you can also have a solo-meal here.
A place where you would take a date, a client, or a small group of friends. Nice ambience and excellent service. You know it's the real deal when platters are served with freshly grated wasabi root.

venue.name: 三井日本料理 Mitsui Cuisine

tip.text: I had the chocolate pop rocks and it was the blandest nitro ice-cream I've had. It wasn't creamy & the flavour wasn't intense. Tasted quite average for something costing 150NT. Disappointed.

venue.name: Cool N2 分子虎 分子雪糕專賣

tip.text: Come here with a friend because you're going to have a tough time finishing the dessert on your own. Their specialty is mango shaved ice but they also have various other flavours and dessert types.

formattedAddress: 忠孝東路四段297號 (延吉街)

tip.text: The Taiwanese breakfast of champions. Try the salty soy milk with 油條（you tiao: literal translation is oil stick). If you're not feeling adventurous, go with the sweet soy milk and dumplings.
If you like the products they stock at Eslite, then this is the place to be. It's everything minus the books.

venue.name: 誠品生活松菸店 Eslite Spectrum Songyan Store

tip.text: Great buffet in a more casual and relaxed ambience. The seafood is fantastic but the warm dishes are so-so. Broad selection of desserts (boasts over 30 choices). I also really enjoyed the juice bar.
Fantastic food and service with panoramic views. Highly recommend the caramelised eggplant and sweet potato fries. Afterwards, head to Monkey Bar next door for a drink.
Authentic Shanghainese cuisine in a low-key setting. Book ahead or you could be waiting well over 30 minutes for a table.

location.crossStreet: M. Huaihai Rd. | 淮海中路
formattedAddress: 41 Tianping Rd. | 天平路41号 (M. Huaihai Rd. | 淮海中路)
ping xing guan rd.1222 (ling shi rd)

venue.name: 大寧劇院 Da Ning Theater

tip.text: Come here for the authentic Taiwanese beef noodles, they're great! Avoid the fried foods as they're just decoys. The owner is from Taiwan and has had the restaurant for over 20 years now.
Fantastic place to stay and great location. It's away from the noisy party-goers. The restaurant is also lovely and delicious.
Good ice cream flavours, but a tad expensive for the servings. Try the vanilla and also the mascarpone fig.
Good breakfast and cosy atmosphere. Try the cheese or deli meats platter.
Great meals, and fantastic service. Try the gnocchi and also the pistachio creme brûlée.
Definitely worth a tour around this historic site. Really interesting, and often shocking artifacts. An hour drive from Prague, or you can visit here by tour bus.
Tickets start from just 1.50 euros -- If you don't mind sitting right at the back with a semi-obstructed view.
Great service, and nice atmosphere. Food was great -- I had the fish soup and seafood risotto. Very hearty and delicious!
